#!/usr/bin/env n6
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# atlas append shard — atlas.n6 SELF-ARCH AXIS-L (axis #12)
# axis-L name: INTRINSIC RAW-AXIOM CITATION + APPEND-ONLY AMENDMENT DSL
# slug: atlas-self-arch-axiom-cite-amendment-evolution
# source: read-only audit of /Users/ghost/core/n6-architecture/atlas/atlas.n6
# follows: D (@-type) + E (meta-tag) + F (arrow K-ceiling) + G (body-field)
#          + H (id-convention) + synthesis (D-H) + I (graph-query primitives)
#          + J (intrinsic supersession DSL) + K (temporal/provenance)
# constraints:
#   raw 22 INFRA-ONLY · raw 23 schema-guard · raw 24 foundation-axiom-immutable
#   raw 91 C3 honest · own#11 strict (no Clay BT 'resolution' claim)
#   raw 117 5-check at registration (genus + 2 cf + 3 channels + counter-ex + falsifier)
#   atlas.n6 + .raw DSL only — NO foreign theory imports as primary lens
#     (event-sourcing append-only logs, RFC 7396 JSON merge patch,
#      git revision history cited-and-moved-on only)
# date: 2026-04-28
# scope contract: this shard does NOT introduce new schema; it PROPOSES axis-L
#                 primitives that follow atlas.n6's existing DSL family
#                 (body-field + meta-tag families — NOT arrow family, sidesteps F K-ceiling)
# pick rationale: TWO axis-L candidates carried (CANDIDATE-A primary, CANDIDATE-B secondary)
#                 because the post-axis-K residual gap-list yielded a 2-way
#                 tie at the empirical-grounding measurement layer:
#                   (A) intrinsic raw-axiom citation DSL — 741 measured textual
#                       citations across 45 distinct raw-N (rank-1 by occurrence)
#                   (B) intrinsic append-only amendment DSL — 36 textual mutation
#                       references + 1 formalised @M loop + axis-K § B7 explicit
#                       deferral of MUTATION territory to axis-L (rank-1 by
#                       deferred-from-prior-axis pointer)
#                 the two close ORTHOGONAL gaps and SHARE registration cost;
#                 carrying both as one shard mirrors axis-I/J co-design pattern
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── §0. PRECISION DEFINITION — what axis-L reifies ───────────
@C atlas-self-arch-axis-l-axiom-cite-amendment-witness :: meta [4!]
  <- raw-23-schema-guard
  <- raw-24-foundation-axiom-immutable
  <- raw-91-C3-honest-disclosure
  <- raw-117-5-check-registration-gate
  <- own#11-strict-no-resolution-claim
  <- atlas-self-arch-axis-i-graph-query-witness
  <- atlas-self-arch-axis-j-supersession-witness
  <- atlas-self-arch-axis-k-temporal-provenance-witness
  introduced_at = 2026-04-28
  origin_shard = atlas-self-arch-axis-l-axiom-cite-amendment-2026-04-28
  -> axis-l-candidate-a-raw-axiom-cite-primitive
  -> axis-l-candidate-b-amendment-primitive
  -> axis-l-orthogonality-vs-D-through-K
  -> axis-l-5-check-results
  -> axis-l-raw-91-C3-disclosures
  => "★ axis-L = TWO INTRINSIC PRIMITIVE FAMILIES, ORTHOGONAL CO-PROPOSAL —"
  => "  L1 = RAW-AXIOM CITATION DSL: a row's dependence on a `.raw` axiom (raw 22 INFRA-ONLY, raw 91 C3 honest, raw 117 5-check, ...) becomes a queryable body-field instead of unstructured prose"
  => "  L2 = APPEND-ONLY AMENDMENT DSL: a row's mid-life evolution (correction, narrowing, refinement WITHOUT retraction) becomes first-class atlas.n6 syntax, closing axis-K § B7's explicit MUTATION-territory deferral"
  => "premise A: atlas.n6 carries 741 textual `raw N` citations across 45 distinct raw-N axioms (raw 91 cited 326×, raw 71 120×, raw 22 77×, raw 24 58×) — the IDIOM exists but the BODY-FIELD does not. axis-I cannot answer 'all rows depending on raw 91' without grep."
  => "premise B: atlas.n6 carries 18 `append-only` invariance assertions + 12 `amendment` references + 3 `no retraction` declarations + 1 formalised @M N6HIST-META-AMEND-3PASS row + 1 'corrected version of iter-55' row — the IDIOM exists but the AMENDMENT-OF-WHICH-ROW back-pointer does not"
  => "today's reality (A): when row X depends on raw 91 honest disclosure, the dependency lives in a `=> \"raw 91 C3 honest: ...\"` prose line OR in a comment header — atlas.n6's DSL cannot answer 'what fraction of consciousness-tier rows cite raw 71?' without grep+regex"
  => "today's reality (B): when row X is amended (e.g. iter-55 finding RETIRED + iter-57 supersession + 3-pass amendment loop), the back-link 'this row amends X' lives ONLY in commit messages + adjacent prose — atlas.n6's DSL has axis-J supersession (replacement) but no AMENDMENT (refinement-without-replacement) primitive"
  => "axis-L1 reifies the raw-axiom dependency channel as DSL primitives belonging to atlas.n6 itself"
  => "axis-L2 reifies the append-only amendment channel, with explicit no-retraction invariant baked into the type signature"
  => "axis-L is the THIRD axis after F (fourth including J, fifth including K) that adds NO new arrow tokens — both L1 and L2 live in axis-G (body-field) family exclusively, deliberately sidestepping the K=10 arrow ceiling (post-axis-I)"

