@C axis-l-5-check-4-counter-example :: meta [4]
  <- axis-l-raw-117-5-check-results
  introduced_at = 2026-04-28
  origin_shard = atlas-self-arch-axis-l-axiom-cite-amendment-2026-04-28
  status = PASS
  counter_example_L1 = "Foundation rows (line 25 @P n = 6 :: foundation [11*]) carry NO explicit raw-axiom binding — they ARE the foundation; the @P axioms PRE-DATE the .raw file's existence as a separate registry. Naive axis-L1 application would force a cites_raw on a row that has no axiom outside itself."
  counter_example_L1_lesson = "axis-L1 cites_raw is OPTIONAL on @P[11*] foundation rows. Required ONLY on @C/@F/@R/@S/@X/@?/@L/@D/@E/@M/@T rows where raw-axiom binding is determinable. Foundation rows MAY carry cites_raw = (empty) as a sentinel value, OR omit the field entirely. Same exemption pattern as axis-K."
  counter_example_L2 = "Rows that are amendments OF amendments (chain depth > 1). Concrete: row Z amends row Y, row Y amends row X. axis-L2 amends accepts ONE slug; amendment chains expressed as Z.amends = Y, Y.amends = X — naive depth-1 lookup loses the X→Y→Z transitive relationship."
  counter_example_L2_lesson = "axis-L2 amends is single-valued (like axis-J superseded_by). Multi-step amendment chains are reconstructed via axis-I <-* amends transitive closure (chain depth tracked structurally, not via multi-valued field). amendment_pass v{N} body-field gives an alternate enumeration when amendments come in PARALLEL passes (like the 3-pass loop) rather than SERIAL chain."
  counter_example_L2_corner = "If row Y amends row X AND row X is later [DEPRECATED] (axis-J), is Y still valid? RESOLUTION: lint emits WARN ('amendment-on-deprecated-target'); legal but unusual; reader interprets as 'historical refinement of a now-superseded claim'. amendment_pass and amended_at preserve the timeline."

@C axis-l-5-check-5-novelty-falsifier :: meta [4]
  <- axis-l-raw-117-5-check-results
  introduced_at = 2026-04-28
  origin_shard = atlas-self-arch-axis-l-axiom-cite-amendment-2026-04-28
  status = PASS
  novelty_claim_L1 = "axis-L1 cites_raw body-field is novel within atlas.n6 — zero current uses (line 1 audit @D axis-l-candidate-a-row-level-cites-body-field = 0)"
  novelty_claim_L2 = "axis-L2 amends body-field is novel within atlas.n6 — zero current uses (line 1 audit @D axis-l-candidate-b-row-level-amends-body-field = 0)"
  falsifier_L1 = "axis-L1 would be FALSIFIED if (a) backfilling cites_raw on existing rows produces collisions where two different rows cite OVERLAPPING raw-N sets in ways that should distinguish them but don't, OR (b) the .raw registry undergoes renumbering and stale cites_raw integers drift, OR (c) raw-N values exceed reasonable encoding (e.g. raw 99999 someday — current max is raw 162, integer-typed accommodates)."
  falsifier_L2 = "axis-L2 would be FALSIFIED if (a) the no-retraction invariant is violated by a future need (e.g. catastrophic atlas.n6 corruption requiring rollback), OR (b) >50% of attempted amendments are actually supersessions misclassified, blurring the L2/J boundary, OR (c) amends chain depth exceeds 5 (combinatorial explosion in <-* traversal cost)."
  falsifier_outcome_L1 = "PARTIAL-FALSIFICATION ACKNOWLEDGED. Falsifier (a) is REAL: of 741 textual raw citations, the prose context disambiguates raw-91 'C3 honest' from raw-91 'rate-of-C3-honesty-checks' — body-field cites_raw = 91 LOSES the prose qualifier. RESOLUTION: cites_raw_purpose body-field can carry the prose qualifier (DEFERRED — would push K_core 22→23, beyond axis-G ceiling). Today: rely on row-level => prose adjacent to cites_raw to carry qualifier."
  falsifier_outcome_L2 = "PARTIAL-FALSIFICATION ACKNOWLEDGED. Falsifier (b) is real boundary case: the J/L2 boundary is JUDGEMENT-DEPENDENT for some rows (e.g. clay-iter-55 was clearly RETIRED but iter-57's relationship was 'definitively replaces' i.e. axis-J supersession; conversely iter-50 NARROWED is clearly amendment). Provide explicit guidance: if the original row's CLAIM is now FALSE, use axis-J (supersession). If the original row's CLAIM is now NARROWER but still valid in the narrower scope, use axis-L2 (amendment)."
  novelty_falsifier_passes_L1 = "by acknowledging the prose-qualifier loss bound and the cites_raw_purpose deferral; axis-L1 is registered with the qualifier-loss escape valve and the optional-on-legacy-rows policy"
  novelty_falsifier_passes_L2 = "by providing the J/L2 boundary criterion (CLAIM-FALSE→J vs CLAIM-NARROWER→L2) at registration time"

